NCI is a leading provider of enterprise solutions and services to U.S. defense, intelligence, health and civilian government agencies. NCI's AI solution, Shai(tm), scales humans with artificial intelligence by empowering the workforce to meet their mission by using best in class AI solutions coupled with our exceptional service offerings. Working with strategic partners, NCI is committed to bringing commercial innovation to missions of national importance. NCI is a mid-tier systems integrator headquartered in Reston, VA, and operates at locations across the globe. 
NCI has been designated a 2020 Military Friendly Employer by MilitaryFriendly.com 
 
Responsibilities:
 
NCI: The Small Business Liaison Officer (SBLO)  will be responsible for NCI's small business program. Position can be worked remotely or from our Reston, Va. office. 
Responsibilities: 
Writes small business subcontracting and participation plans for inclusion in proposals 
Administers NCI's small business subcontracting and participation plans 
Prepares and submits ISR/SSR and other small business reports 
Represents NCI during small business audits/reviews 
Administers NCI's vendor rating program 
Will have other Procurement related responsibilities that may include material purchasing, subcontract labor purchasing, CPSR audit prep 
Other duties as assigned 
Qualifications:
 
Requirements: 
Bachelorâ€™s Degree or equivalent related experience 
2 - 7 Years experience as a Small Business Liaison Officer or equivalent, to include writing small business subcontracting and participation plans 
Preferred Education and Experience: 
Experience as a Buyer or Subcontracts Administrator supporting a government approved purchasing system 
Physical Requirements: 
This position requires the ability to perform the below essential functions: 
Sitting for long periods 
Standing for long periods 
Ambulate throughout an office 
Ambulate between several buildings 
